718→### 2.6  Optimistic UI with `pending_ops`
719→
720→One subtle refinement: when the user clicks "Stage", the status list should
721→update **immediately** without waiting for the background job to complete and
722→the status to be refreshed (which can take ~50–200ms on large repos).
723→
724→```rust
725→pub enum PendingOp {
726→    Staging,    // file is being staged
727→    Unstaging,  // file is being unstaged
728→}
729→```
730→
731→Before sending the job, `Repository` records the pending state:
732→
733→```rust
734→fn stage_entries(&mut self, paths: Vec<RepoPath>, cx: &mut Context<Self>) {
735→    for path in &paths {
736→        self.pending_ops.insert(path.clone(), PendingOp::Staging);
737→    }
738→    cx.notify(); // render with optimistic state immediately
739→
740→    let (tx, rx) = oneshot::channel();
741→    self.job_sender.send(GitJob::StageEntries { paths: paths.clone(), tx }).ok();
742→
743→    // When the job completes, clear pending_ops and notify again:
744→    let entity = cx.entity().downgrade();
745→    cx.spawn(|_window, cx| async move {
746→        if rx.await.is_ok() {
747→            entity.update(cx, |repo, cx| {
748→                for path in &paths { repo.pending_ops.remove(path); }
749→                cx.notify();
750→            }).ok();
751→        }
752→    }).detach();
753→}
754→```
755→
756→The `GitPanel::render_entry()` checks `pending_ops` to show a spinner or
757→tentative checkbox state:
758→
759→```rust
760→let effective_staged = if repo.pending_ops.contains_key(&entry.repo_path) {
761→    PendingOp::Staging => CheckboxState::Checked,    // show as staged
762→    PendingOp::Unstaging => CheckboxState::Unchecked, // show as unstaged
763→} else {
764→    entry.staging_state()  // derived from GitFileStatus
765→};
766→```
