820→### 2.8  The AskPass Credential System
821→
822→Remote operations require a way to prompt the user for credentials without
823→blocking the main thread. Zed implements this with a custom askpass helper.
824→
825→```
826→git push (subprocess)
827→    ↓
828→GIT_ASKPASS=/path/to/zed-askpass
829→    ↓
830→zed-askpass binary (tiny C program, just calls a Unix socket)
831→    ↓
832→Unix socket ← ZEDASKPASS_SOCKET_PATH env var
833→    ↓
834→Zed main process receives credential request
835→    ↓
836→GitStore looks up AskPassDelegate by ZEDASKPASS_DELEGATE_ID
837→    ↓
838→AskPassDelegate sends prompt to UI layer (shows modal)
839→    ↓
840→User types password → sent back through the socket
841→    ↓
842→zed-askpass receives the password string → writes to stdout
843→    ↓
844→git receives the credential
