882→### 2.9  Remote Mode (`GitStoreMode::Remote`)
883→
884→In SSH remote development, the **client** machine has a `GitStore` in
885→`Remote` mode that caches snapshots for display but routes all write
886→operations to the **host** via protobuf RPC.
887→
888→```rust
889→// On the client side (GitStore in Remote mode):
890→fn stage_entries(&self, paths: Vec<RepoPath>, cx: &mut Context<Self>) {
891→    match &self.mode {
892→        GitStoreMode::Local => { /* submit job to Repository */ }
893→        GitStoreMode::Remote { upstream } => {
894→            upstream.request(proto::StageEntries {
895→                project_id: REMOTE_SERVER_PROJECT_ID,
896→                paths: paths.iter().map(|p| p.to_proto()).collect(),
897→            });
898→        }
899→    }
900→}
901→
902→// The host's GitStore registers RPC handlers:
903→fn shared(&mut self, project_id: u64, client: AnyProtoClient, cx: &mut Context<Self>) {
904→    client.add_request_handler(cx.entity(), Self::handle_stage_entries);
905→    client.add_request_handler(cx.entity(), Self::handle_unstage_entries);
906→    // ...
907→}
908→
909→async fn handle_stage_entries(
910→    this: Entity<GitStore>,
911→    envelope: TypedEnvelope<proto::StageEntries>,
912→    cx: AsyncApp,
913→) -> Result<proto::Ack> {
914→    this.update(cx, |store, cx| {
915→        // Runs the local job queue path
916→        store.stage_entries_local(paths, cx);
917→    })?;
918→    Ok(proto::Ack {})
919→}
920→```
921→
922→The `proto/git.proto` file defines the full RPC surface:
923→
924→```protobuf
925→message StageEntries { uint64 project_id = 1; repeated string paths = 2; }
926→message UnstageEntries { uint64 project_id = 1; repeated string paths = 2; }
927→message SetIndexText { uint64 project_id = 1; string path = 2; optional string content = 3; }
928→message Commit { uint64 project_id = 1; string message = 2; bool amend = 3; bool signoff = 4; }
929→message UpdateRepository { /* full repository snapshot for client cache */ }
930→```
931→
932→The `UpdateRepository` message is sent from host to client whenever a
933→`Repository` entity's status changes, updating the client's cached display
934→state without the client needing to run `git status` itself.
